1. d4 {Hello and welcome to my course on the Semi-Slav! I have often been asked what is the best chess opening for White and Black. Of course, it is impossible to give a definite answer, but it is an interesting question as to how to evaluate different openings. This is especially relevant in this age, when we can equalise in practically every decent opening with strong computers. For me, there are a few main points to evaluate when we consider an opening for Black: A It has to be fundamentally sound and Black should be able to equalise comfortably in every line. B It has to be fighting: Black should have the chance to take over the position if White does not play accurately. C We should be able to play it for a long time, which means there should be some variety in the main lines. The Semi-Slav is one of the very few openings that ticks all the above boxes. It is sound and gives Black good fighting chances. The main lines have several different options we can go for. Even though there are two excellent courses on Chessable already, I give completely different options in the main lines. It’s always great to have a choice, and this makes it difficult for your opponent to prepare. This course will be a complete repertoire against 1.d4 starting with all the alternatives on move two. We will start with the main lines first, and then slowly scale our way back. I go for some new and exciting ideas in the Meran, Anti-Meran and the Botvinnik, which have not been explored much. These are the most critical lines where White is fighting for the advantage. I have been playing the Semi-Slav for more than 8 years and I am giving you my latest polished repertoire. The big advantage of not playing chess competitively anymore is that I can afford to publish all my analyses without hiding anything. Everything has been checked in detail by the latest cloud engines, and I have played most of these lines myself with great results. I hope you will enjoy going through the course as much as I did making it. As with my previous course on the Italian, I will answer all your questions in the forums. I look forward to hearing your feedback and any suggestions that you may have. Good luck in your journey with the Semi-Slav!} *

