{Immediately after the Introduction, we will have the Quickstarter guide, which is one of my favourite features of Chessable. It gives you a good overview of the most important lines across the course. You could immediately start playing the Semi-Slav after learning the Quickstarter lines, and refer to the main chapters whenever you have any doubts. If you have more time, I would definitely recommend going through the full course as you get a better understanding of the typical plans and ideas. We will start with the most important lines in the Semi-Slav. The main course is divided into 4 sections. Each of these sections will start with an overview, where I give a brief introduction to the overall variation. I explain why I chose my recommendation and how it compares to the other options. I will also give a few model games in each of these overviews. I do have to warn you that you might be subjected to a few of my not-quite-masterpieces — to help boost my delicate ego. :-} 1. Z0 *

