ade the bishops.} 16. Ne5 Bxc5 17. Bf4 Bd6 {[%csl Re5][%cal Gf6e4] White has a lot of problems with the [e5]-knight. It cannot retreat easily now.} 18. Rfd1 $2 {White does not understand our threat.} Nd5 $19 {[%csl Rc3,Rf4] All of this happened in the game 0-1 22 Kazhgaleyev,M 2607-Anand,V 2792 Bastia 2006. White is forced to take on [d5] which also opens the e-file.} *

