1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. Qc2 Bd6 7. a3 {[%csl Gc5][%cal Gb2b4] We are going to start with some of the more obscure sidelines. White wants to play [c5] or [b4] next, but is compromising their development.} O-O 8. b4 ({If} 8. c5 Bc7 {we will continue with ...[e5] with a great position.}) 8... a5 {We immediately fight back on the queenside.} 9. b5 c5 $1 {[%csl Re1] It is time to break the centre with White's king still stuck there. It would be amazing to open the e-file with a future ...[e5].} 10. dxc5 Nxc5 11. Bb2 Qe7 $15 {[%cal Ge6e5,Ge5e4] We are ready to play ...[e5]-[e4]. White is in trouble due to their lack of development.} *

