is is the usual square for the queen in these lines. We will bring our [f8]-rook to [d8] next.} 16. Rad1 Rfd8 {I like to put this rook on [d8], as it gives us the chance to bring our king to the centre faster if we reach an endgame.} 17. Ne5 Ne4 $13 {[%cal Gf7f6,Ge6e5] We finally trade the queens with the added benefit that we will get the move ...[f6] with a tempo.} *

