 queen gets out of the way of the rook on [c8].} h6 {This is our usual useful waiting move on the kingside before we go for our ideas in the centre.} 14. h3 c5 {We are happy to accept a hanging pawns structure. Even though hanging pawns are often considered a weakness, they can help us easily take over the initiative at the right moment.} 15. cxd5 exd5 16. Bf1 Nf8 $10 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gf8e6] The knight is heading to [e6] to keep a better eye on the centre. If White does end up taking on [c5], we will always have the potential idea of ...[d4], releasing the energy of our pieces.} *

