We play the same as we did in the previous line. Let White show us their plan first.} 14. g3 Bb4 {[%csl Rc3][%cal Gc6c5] This is a very typical idea in these positions, preparing the move ...[c5]. The bishop puts more pressure along the c-file.} 15. Bg2 c5 16. cxd5 Bxc3 $1 {This is the point: we trade off our dark-squared bishop as the kingside pawns were restricting it.} 17. Qxc3 Bxd5 $10 {[%cal Gc5c4,Ga7a5,Ga5a4] We are threatening to play ...[c4] next. Another plan is to continue with ...[a5]-[a4] on the queenside.} *

