 the centre.} 15. Qh4 c5 {[%cal Gf6e4] White is unable to play [d5] with their rook still on [f1]. We are planning to play ...[Ne4] next, trading the queens.} 16. dxc5 {White opens up the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop, but gives us an amazing square on [c5] for our bishop as well.} Bxc5 17. Ne5 Rad8 {We bring our last piece into the game, fighting for the d-file.} 18. Bd3 Ne4 {It is time to trade the queens with all our pieces being well placed for the endgame.} 19. Qf4 {White tries to keep the queens on the board.} Qf6 $10 {[%csl Rf4] Of course, we do not want to allow this. Now there is no escape from the queen trade, and we reach a comfortable endgame. We can bring the king into the center much faster compared to White.} *

