xd4 Be5 {[%cal Gc6c5,Ge5c3] We want to play ...[c5] and trade the bishops.} 22. f4 f5 $1 {We create a square on [f6] for the bishop, allowing us to keep our dark-squared bishop alive.} 23. Qg3 Bf6 24. Nxe6 $1 {This is objectively the best for White, leading to a forced draw.} Rxd1 25. Ng5 Rexe1+ 26. Bxe1 Qh5 {We did have a few options, but this forces White to take a draw.} 27. Nf7+ Kg8 28. Nh6+ Kh8 $10 {As with all good lines, this too leads to a draw by repetition. :-} *

