 19. Rb1 Bf6 20. bxc6 Ba6 {We stop White from castling. We want to play ...[Rc8] and win the pawn on [c6]. This is the only danger in the position.} 21. Nb4 Bc3+ 22. Kd1 Bb5 23. h4 Bxb4 24. Rxb4 Bxc6 $10 {We have a passed pawn on the queenside, but the opposite colour bishops ensure that there is a huge drawing margin.} *

