al, but we want to target the [d4]-pawn. White cannot exploit the pin immediately.} 20. O-O Qc7 {We get out of the pin with a tempo.} 21. h3 Rd8 $10 {Now White is forced to give up the bishop for our knight, and we reach a major piece endgame. White can win the pawn on [a7], but we will start attacking on the kingside. We can also win the [d4]-pawn with ...[Qb6].} *

