1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. g3 {We will now consider the sidelines on move 5. The Fianchetto system is a decent try against all openings after 1.d4. It can be tried on different moves. Here, the drawback is the knight on [c3]. It is usually better placed on [d2] to defend the [c4]-pawn.} dxc4 {We take up the challenge. Generally against the fianchetto bishop, I prefer to keep my pawn on [d5] as it restricts the bishop on [g2]. We have cemented it with both the pawns on [c6] and [e6]. At the same time, the knight is misplaced on [c3]. This gives us the chance to go ...[b5]-[b4] on the queenside after we win the pawn on [c4]. White, on the other hand, focuses on building up their centre.} 6. Bg2 Nbd7 7. O-O {This is the most common move, preparing to play [e4] next. White is not too bothered about the missing pawn and instead wants to advance in the centre. I think this is the more critical approach and we need to be careful.} b5 {We defend the pawn on [c4] and gain space on the queenside. The added benefit is that we can kick the knight from [c3] with ...[b4] at any moment.} 8. Ng5 {This is a tricky move to face over the board. I have been a victim of this in two Titled Tuesday games on chess.com. Please learn from my mistakes! :-} Qb6 $1 {This is the strongest reply in my opinion, as we keep the knight on [f6] which makes our position more secure.} ({I went for} 8... Nd5 {in one of my games. Although it is fine for Black, I feel it may be hard to play over the board.} 9. e4 Nxc3 10. bxc3 h6 $2 {I cannot believe I blundered like this, but I forgot about the bishop coming via the queenside.} 11. Nxe6 fxe6 12. Qh5+ Ke7 13. Ba3+ {+-}) 9. b3 {This is White's best move, opening up the queenside.} h6 {We can play this safely now. White's knight is forced to go back.} 10. Nge4 cxb3 11. Qxb3 Nd5 {[%csl Gd5] We cement our knight in the middle of the board. White has to take on [d5] to equalise. This improves our pawn structure and makes our life much easier in the centre.} 12. Nxd5 cxd5 13. Nc3 b4 14. Na4 Qd8 $10 {Our work is done with our centre secured. Next, we will look to get our king to safety as soon as we can, with a comfortable position.} *

