re.} (13. Be2 {runs into} Bb4+ {with a comfortable position for Black.}) 13... Nd7 $1 {We continue developing our pieces, temporarily sacrificing the bishop on [b7]. We turn the tables as now White's king is more vulnerable. We will win the piece back on [b2].} 14. Qxb7 {There was no other option for White in order to maintain equality.} Qa5+ $1 {It's good to include this check, forcing White's king to stay in the centre.} 15. Kd1 Rb8 16. Qxa6 Qxa6 17. Bxa6 Rxb2 $10 {[%csl Rf2][%cal Gb2f2] All of this happened in the game between Christopher Yoo and the famous Youtuber Levy Rozman. We will win the pawn on [f2] next. The endgame is balanced, as the strong a-pawn compensates for our piece activity.} *

