ht to [d5].} 14. Nxg6 hxg6 15. Qc2 {White threatens to take on [g6], but this is not a deadly threat.} exd4 16. exd4 Nb6 17. Bb3 Qd7 $10 {[%csl Rd4,Gd5][%cal Ga7a5,Ga5a4] We go after the [d4]-pawn instead and achieve everything that we were aiming for. The knight is heading to [d5] and we can play ...[a5]-[a4] on the queenside. We are on the better side of equality.} *

