 chain, we have no issues defending the [d5]-pawn. The [b7]-pawn is in some trouble, though.} 14. Qxb7 {This is the only way for White to justify their play.} Nxg3 15. hxg3 Qd6 {[%cal Gf8b8,Gc6b4] We defend the knight on [c6]. Another point is that we are planning to go after the [b2]-pawn, and we discourage White from bringing the queen to [a3].} 16. Qa6 Rab8 17. Na4 {[%csl Gb2,Gb6] White stops ...[Rb6] and defends the [b2]-pawn at the same time.} Qb4+ 18. Nd2 Na5 $1 {We attack the knight on [a4] and open up the c-file for our rooks.} 19. b3 Rfc8 $36 {[%cal Gg3g4,Gf5g6,Gc8c2]} (19... Rfc8 {All our pieces are joining the party and the rook is heading to c2. White has to be careful with the king still stuck on e1. Keep in mind that we meet the move} 20. g4 {with} Bg6 {first before heading in with the rook.}) *

