o equal.}) 10. Be5 {White wants to trade off our beautiful bishop on [g7].} Nxc3 {We do not have much of an option, but we will weaken White's structure on the queenside.} 11. Qxc3 Qxc3+ 12. Bxc3 Bxc3+ 13. bxc3 dxc4 $10 {[%cal Gb8d7] We are going to win the [c5]-pawn with ...[Nd7] next. The endgame is perfectly equal, as White will also give up the pawn with the move [c6], breaking our structure.} *

