hite, getting the bishop to [b2] first.} Bd6 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gd8e7] We do not need the bishop on [e7] now to stop White from playing [e4], as they are playing very slowly, developing the bishop to [b2] first. The bishop on [d6] keeps an eye on the [e5]-square and also gives us a square for the queen on [e7].} 9. Bb2 O-O 10. Ne5 {This knight is not doing much on [e5]. We can just ignore it.} Qe7 {I want to bring the rook to [d8] next. We will take on [e5] at the right moment.} 11. a3 Rfd8 {The rook on [a8] will be more useful on the queenside. Either along the a-file or the c-file.} 12. Re1 a5 $36 {[%cal Gf6e4] We have developed all our pieces and they are reasonably well-placed. We can look to play ...[Ne4] next.} *

