t, which will stop White from playing [b5]. This does not work well with the knight on [b8], as we will see.} 12. h3 {White intends to gain some space on the kingside. The best square for the [c1]-bishop would be on the [h2]-[b8] diagonal.} Nbd7 13. g4 Bh7 14. Bf4 Ne4 {We trade minor pieces as we have less space compared to our opponent. Also, we prepare the move ...[f5] to open up the f-file.} 15. e3 f5 $1 {[%cal Gf8f4,Gg7g5] For a change, we go after the white kingside.} 16. gxf5 Bxf5 $10 {[%csl Rh3][%cal Gg7g5] We will play ...[g5] next. The [e5]-square is not a big deal. We have created a weakness on [h3] which we can target in the future.} *

