l free up the centre for their pieces. However, at the same time, the [d4]-pawn becomes a big liability.} a5 {[%cal Ga5a4] The knight is going to move away from [c3] and we are ready to exploit this with the ...[a4] advance.} 11. e4 (11. a3 {can be met with} Re8 {. We are preparing to play ...[Bf8] and ...[e5]. We are happy to allow White to play [e4], weakening their centre.}) 11... dxe4 12. Ndxe4 Nxe4 13. Nxe4 a4 $1 {We will maintain the pawn on [a4] for as long as possible, as it is a constant nuisance for our opponent to deal with.} 14. Qe2 Nf6 $10 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Ge7f6,Gf6b2] We are aiming to get all the minor pieces except the dark-squared bishops off the board. Our bishop will be better on [f6], targeting [d4]. We are more comfortable than White here.} *

