r trade or kick White's knight back.} 12. Qb3 Qb6 {[%cal Gb6b3] We go for our standard reaction to the move [Qb3]. We do not mind taking on [b3] next move to trade the queens.} 13. Be3 (13. Qc3 {is an option for White to keep the queens on the board, but the drawback is that after} Nf6 {White cannot retreat back to [c3] with the knight.}) 13... Qxb3 {We do not want to give White the option to keep the queens with [Qc3] next move.} 14. axb3 a6 $10 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gf8d8,Gd7f6] Black is comfortable with no weaknesses. The endgame should be balanced with White having more space but also more weaknesses than us.} *

