1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 {Finally we come to the dreaded Slav Exchange. This was one of the reasons why I started playing the Nimzo move order to reach the Semi-Slav. 3.cxd5 is a common move across all levels, and in many cases, White is happy to make a draw. This is a challenge, as we would need to take undue risks to get a complicated game.Instead, my approach is simple: as much as possible I will try to give the more complex option if it is objectively fine for us. Our focus should be to play a long game and try to outplay our opponent. At the same time, it is very much possible that White will try to fight for an advantage in these lines.} cxd5 {White has three different ways to reach the main lines. They can start with either [Bf4], [Nc3] or [Nf3]. It is better to delay the development of the [g1] knight as it can come to [e2] in some lines.} 4. Bg5 ({I have faced this move twice against very strong opponents. Someone who plays} 4. Bg5 {is likely looking for a fight, and this is exactly what we are hoping too. There are several much safer lines for White to try to make a draw.}) 4... f6 {A very unusual move, but we are getting a tempo against the bishop and it is useful to gain space in the centre. We are very ambitious and want to play ...[e5] soon.} 5. Bh4 {White commits the bishop to the kingside, stopping the move ...[e5] for now.} Nh6 $1 {[%csl Rh4][%cal Gh6f5] Another unusual idea, which works very well here. The knight is heading to [f5] and the bishop on [h4] cannot escape.} 6. Nc3 Nf5 7. Bg3 Nc6 {[%cal Gh7h5,Gh5h4,Gg3b8]} ({We are not going to capture on g3 immediately. Instead, we will try to further harass the bishop with ...h5-h4. If we played} 7... h5 {directly, White could take on [b8]. So instead we develop the knight first, attacking the [d4]-pawn.}) 8. e3 h5 9. Be2 g6 $36 {[%cal Gh5h4,Gg3f4,Gg6g5] The threat of ...[h4] and ...[g5] is impossible to stop unless White wants to wreck their kingside.} (9... g6 {White has to play very accurately now with} 10. Nf3 h4 11. Bf4 g5 12. Bxg5 fxg5 13. Nxg5 Ng7 {and it looks like we have defended everything. The engine still finds some ways to maintain the balance with White though.}) *

