te's bishop.} 8. Be2 {This is the most played move in the position, defending the [f3]-knight with the bishop. Even then, the bishop is not doing much there on [f3].} e6 9. O-O Bd6 {As usual, we want to trade the dark-squared bishops.} 10. Bxd6 {I don't think any of White's other options are particularly impressive. White might as well trade on [d6] immediately, without wasting time.} Qxd6 11. h3 {White forces us to trade on [f3], but this does waste a tempo.} Bxf3 12. Bxf3 O-O 13. Rc1 Rac8 {We are going to double rooks on the c-file.} 14. Qd2 Rc7 15. Na4 Rfc8 $10 {[%cal Ge6e5] We will go for the ...[e5] break soon, especially if White brings the knight to [c5]. There is still play left in the position.} *

