ll in the centre.} Bd6 {The bishop is best placed here, especially in the lines with ...[Ne4].} 10. cxd5 exd5 {[%cal Ge8g8,Gd8e7] If given a couple of moves to castle kingside and go ...[Qe7], we are just better.} 11. dxc5 {This creates an interesting dilemma for us how to recapture the pawn.} Ndxc5 $1 {We are not too concerned about the check on [b5]. This is definitely the most ambitious recapture, and all our pieces are now on their ideal squares.} 12. Bb5+ Kf8 $36 {[%csl Gb7,Gd6,Ge4][%cal Gh7h5,Gh8h6] Our king is safe on [f8]. All our pieces are looking towards the kingside and we can play ...[h5] next, bringing the rook into the game via [h6].} *

