1. d4 d5 2. h3 ({Another move which has been tried by Hikaru. This seems like more of a troll move than} 2. a3 {, as I can see no genuine reason to play 2.h3 .}) 2... Nf6 {Our reaction will be the exact the same for all these moves. Consistency is a very underrated part of building a solid repertoire.} 3. Nf3 c5 4. e3 e6 {[%cal Gb8d7,Gb7b6,Gc8b7,Gf8e7,Ge8g8] Our plan now is to put the knight on [d7] and play ...[b6] and ...[Bb7] on the queenside. Our dark-squared bishop can go to either [e7] or [d6] and then we castle kingside.} 5. Bb5+ {White tries to mess with our development. This was played in a rapid game between Maghsoodloo, P and Warmerdam, M.} Nbd7 {We do not deviate. We will kick the bishop back next move and continue with our plan.} 6. O-O a6 7. Be2 b6 $10 {[%cal Gc8b7,Gf8e7,Ge8h8] I think we can stop here already. Our plan is pretty simple. We can take on [d4] at the right moment once White goes for the move [b3]. I do not want to give you long sample lines for no reason.} *

